programme.title: Clash of the Titans
programme.desc: Perseus, the son of Zeus, is caught in a war between gods and is helpless to save his family from Hades. With nothing left to lose, Perseus leads a dangerous quest to prevent Hades from overthrowing the king of the gods and laying waste to Earth.

programme.title: Wrath of the Titans
programme.desc: Perseus (Sam Worthington) enlists the aid of Queen Andromeda (Rosamund Pike), Hephaestus (Bill Nighy) and Poseidons son (Toby Kebbell) to rescue Zeus (Liam Neeson) from the underworld, defeat the Titans and save mankind.

programme.title: The Last Witch Hunter
programme.desc: The fate of the human race hangs in the balance when the Witch Queen (Julie Engelbrecht) rises from the dead, seeking revenge against Kaulder (Vin Diesel), the immortal warrior who slayed her centuries ago.

programme.title: Bloodshot
programme.desc: Killed in action, soldier Ray Garrison gets a new lease on life when the RST Corp. brings him back from the dead. But when the company decides to manipulate his mind and memories, Ray must embark on a mission to find out whats real and whats not.

programme.title: Dead Shot
programme.desc: When a border ambush goes wrong, an ex-paramilitary soldier witnesses the fatal shooting of his pregnant wife by a British sergeant. Wounded and presumed dead, he escapes and takes his revenge to the dark and paranoid streets of 1970s London.

programme.title: Project Gutenberg
programme.desc: The Hong Kong police hunt for a counterfeiting gang led by a mastermind known as Painter. In an effort to find Painters real identity, the police recruit artist Lee Man.

programme.title: Line Walker 2: Invisible Spy
programme.desc: A car crash causes a war between local police and an international terrorist organization.

programme.title: Superman: The Movie
programme.desc: Jor-El (Marlon Brando) of Krypton sends his baby to Earth, where he grows up as Clark Kent (Christopher Reeve) and works at the Daily Planet.

programme.title: Red
programme.desc: Retired CIA agents (Bruce Willis, Morgan Freeman, John Malkovich) reassemble for survival after the agency sends assassins to silence them and the secrets they carry.

programme.title: Superman II
programme.desc: The Man of Steel (Christopher Reeve) gets serious with Lois Lane (Margot Kidder) and fights three Krypton outcasts in league with Lex Luthor (Gene Hackman).

programme.title: Hard Kill
programme.desc: Mercenaries race against the clock to stop a madman from using a computer program to wreak havoc around the globe.

programme.title: Gran Torino
programme.desc: An unlikely friendship forms between a bigoted war veteran (Clint Eastwood) and an Asian boy (Bee Vang) who tried to steal the mans treasured automobile.

programme.title: The Mule
programme.desc: Broke and facing foreclosure on his business, a 90-year-old horticulturist takes a job as a drug courier for a Mexican cartel. His immediate success leads to easy money and a larger shipment that soon draws the attention of a hard-charging DEA agent.

programme.title: Cry Macho
programme.desc: A one-time rodeo star and washed-up horse breeder takes a job from his ex-boss to bring the mans son home from Mexico. Forced to take the back roads to Texas, the world-weary horseman finds unexpected connections and his own sense of redemption.

programme.title: John Wick 3: Parabellum
programme.desc: Stripped of the High Tables protective services, legendary hit man John Wick must fight his way through the streets of New York as the worlds most ruthless killers try to collect the $14 million bounty on his head.

programme.title: Bull
programme.desc: Ten years after he was last seen, a vicious mob enforcer returns home to find his son and methodically track down the gang that double-crossed him. His quest for revenge soon leads to a savage showdown between his wife and her mob boss father.

programme.title: Braven
programme.desc: A logger and his father head to their hunting cabin, hoping for a quiet weekend. Instead, they find themselves in a kill-or-be-killed stand for survival when they encounter a gang of ruthless drug traffickers.

programme.title: Haul Out the Holly
programme.desc: Emily comes home to visit her parents, only to discover theyre leaving for a trip of their own. While staying at their house for the holidays, Emily meets members of the community who want her to join in the neighborhoods Christmas festivities.

programme.title: Next Stop, Christmas
programme.desc: Angie wonders what life would be like if she had married an ex who became famous. When she finds herself magically transported into the past, Angie has the chance to relive that Christmas and learn what (and who) is truly important to her.

programme.title: Where Are You, Christmas?
programme.desc: Addy wishes for a year without Christmas and wakes up in a black-and-white world. She must work together with the town mechanic to restore the holiday to all its glory.

programme.title: Christmas Connection
programme.desc: Sydney is tasked with looking after Leah, an unaccompanied minor. After Leah is safely delivered, Sydney finds a package Leah left behind and decides to deliver it. When she misses her connection, she is invited to spend the holidays with them.

programme.title: Boyfriends of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Marketing executive Lauren must learn to open her heart with the help of four ghosts of ex-boyfriends who visit her leading up to Christmas.

programme.title: Creating Christmas
programme.desc: Aspiring illustrator Harper collaborates with demanding author Caleb. When he insists on working through Christmas in a quaint town, she must use the holiday celebrations to help break his writers block.

programme.title: Meet Me at the Christmas Train Parade
programme.desc: When Charlottes son Benny learns about an old tradition, he persuades her to try and reignite the Christmas magic that brought neighboring communities together.

programme.title: Scary Stories to Tell in the Dark
programme.desc: On Halloween 1968, Stella and her two friends meet a mysterious drifter, Ramon, and uncover a sinister notebook of stories.

programme.title: Hollywood on Set
programme.desc: Features behind-the-scenes footage from movie sets and discussions with the cast and crew about the details of each film.

programme.title: Jingle Bell Bride
programme.desc: A wedding planner finds romance with a handsome local after traveling to a remote town in Alaska to find a rare flower for a celebrity client.

programme.title: Christmas Getaway
programme.desc: After a surprising breakup with her boyfriend, a travel writer decides to go on the picturesque Christmas vacation planned for the two of them, alone.

programme.title: Christmas Wishes and Mistletoe Kisses
programme.desc: Weeks before Christmas, an interior designer is hired to decorate the estate of a wealthy businessman.

programme.title: On the 12th Date of Christmas
programme.desc: Two seemingly incompatible game designers in Chicago team up to create a romantic city-wide scavenger hunt to promote a hotel chain.

programme.title: A Holiday Hideout
programme.desc: An upstanding female private detective named Jessie goes undercover to guard two people in the witness protection program.

programme.title: A Biltmore Christmas
programme.desc: A magical hourglass sends modern-day screenwriter Lucy Hardgrove to the set of the 1947 holiday movie classic "His Merry Wife!" However, before she can return to the present, Lucy must make things right or threaten to alter the future forever.

programme.title: Santa Tell Me
programme.desc: A design show host finds a letter from Santa promising to meet her true love, a man named Nick, by Christmas Eve. Meeting three Nicks complicates her search.

programme.title: Arthur Christmas

programme.title: Christmas at the Plaza
programme.desc: When historian Jessica is hired to create the Plazas Christmas display, she finds more than facts while teaming up with handsome decorator Nick to bring the display to life.
